5:
DON'T LET UP, SNOWPAWS! DRINK
THAT BOY INTO THE GROUND!
10: What do you think you're doing?
18:
Yeah. Like this hooting crowd of
monkeys would be here to watch
you have "a" drink.
32:
Hey, barkeep! I'm ready for pint
number twenty-ONE!
38: It's a close race, me hearties!
39:
YOO-HOO! SNOWPAWS! I'm bettin' a
whole week's salary on ya!
40:
EY! Whatever I put on Selgir? DOUBLE
IT!
43:
No shame in backing down now,
Nimbus.
55: I would also like a pint.
64:
HEEELP! There's a man-eating shark
by the beach!
68:
Man... Just when things were getting
interesting.
72:
Let's go. For fisherfolk, this is a
life-or-death situation.
76:
Yeah, yeah... HEY, BARKEEP! I'm leavin'
the money here!
86:
Yeah. All the drinking put me in the
mood for shark-fin soup.
92: Are you SURE you're not gonna puke?
98:
Please. Might as well have been
drinking mountain spring water.
113:
Hah. Gotta admit, I can't compete
with you on the waves.
115:
You up for another round of drinking
when we get back? We gotta
celebrate this hunt!
118:
Yeah. But after I finish maintaining
my gun.
122:
You really care about that gun. Is
there some kind of story behind it?
125:
A long time ago, I was captured by
pirates. The same pirates that took
my right eye.
128:
Among their crew, there was a
man... Strange. Eccentric. He was the
one who gave me this gun.
129: And taught me how to use it.
138: I can't shoot with one eye.
140:
Try sayin' that to one of yer foes, and
I guarantee they'll be takin' more
than an eye.
145:
You got more backbone than most
Gaean dogs. Be a shame if you
retired so early.
146:
Get enough experience in ya, and
next time we meet, Selgir, you might
have ME in ropes.
153:
Wow... You must have a bunch of
memories wrapped up in
168:
Don't worry. If there's one thing that
man taught me, it was never to miss.
173:
That's so cool! You must've put in so
much training!
174:
...Think you could tell me more about
being a pirate?
176:
Sure. When you're old enough to
drink.
178:
It's not something I like to talk about
sober.
182:
Wait. So I've gotta wait until YOU'RE
drunk? I don't think my liver can
handle that...
187: Alk, why don't you drink juice instead?
191:
Stella... You're a genius! And that
means we can listen to Selgir's
stories tonight!
196:
Learn to open up a little, Selgir. We're
all friends here. And if you need a
drinkin' buddy, who better than me,
right?
